transcript.text: If   monkeys   have   one   banana,   banana   rare,   banana   valuable.   Ahh!   But   if
monkeys   grow   more   bananas,   banana   become   common,   banana   not   as   valuable.   Demand-pull
inflation.   If   monkeys   demand   more   banana,   but   banana   farmer   makes   same   amount,
banana   price   go   up   because   banana   more   rare.   Ahh!   Cost-push   inflation.   If
banana   demand   is   the   same,   but   banana   farmer   have   less   banana   to
sell,   banana   price   go   up   because   banana   become   more   rare.   Ahh!   Production
cost   inflation.   Monkey   buys   banana.   Monkey   eat   banana.   Life   is   good.   Monkey
tell   monkey   friends   about   banana   store.   Monkeys   buy   all   the   bananas.   Banana
farmer   has   to   plant   more   banana   tree,   but   banana   seed   become   more
expensive,   so   banana   farmer   raise   price   of   banana   to   cover   cost.   Monetary
inflation.   If   banana   demand   is   the   same   and   banana   supply   is   the
same,   but   monkeys   have   more   leaves   than   usual   to   buy   banana,   banana
price   go   up,   because   now   leaves   are   not   worth   as   much   as
before.   Hyperinflation.   Price   of   banana   goes   up,   so   monkey   government   decides   to
create   more   leaves   so   monkeys   can   afford   banana.   So   monkey   buy   more
banana,   but   banana   price   goes   up   to   keep   up   with   banana   demand,
so   monkey   government   creates   more   leaves.   But   price   of   banana   goes   up
to   keep   up   with   more   demand,   so   monkey   government   creates   more   leaves.
But   price   of   banana   goes   up,   so   monkey   government   creates   more   leaves.
This   is   getting   ridiculous.   Eventually,   monkey   government   burns   all   the   leaves   and
starts   making   sticks,   its   new   currency.   Inflation   is   not   necessarily   bad   for
monkey.   If   monkeys'   amount   of   leaves   goes   up   at   the   same   rate
as   price   of   banana,   monkey   happy.   If   monkeys'   amount   of   leaves   goes
up,   but   banana   price   stays   the   same,   monkey   rich   as   fu-...   If
monkeys'   leaves   stay   the   same,   but   banana   price   go   up,   monkey   poor,
monkey   sad.   Monkey   is   all   of   us.   To   avoid   inflation,   monkey   should
invest   banana,   as   this   will   grow   more   banana   with   time.   Sometimes   inflation
can   get   really   bananas.   Please   subscribe.   (instrumental music plays)
